Great chargrilled oysters! Their ostrich chili is amazing, as well as their split pea and pork belly soup! Haven't had a bad meal yet here and the staff is super friendly and welcoming! Lots of tvs to watch whatever game you want! Highly recommend this place of your visiting New Orleans in the French Quarter!

MRB is the best local bar in the French Quarter. Their food, cocktails, craft brews, courtyards, and LIVE entertainment are incredible. The servers and bartenders are always friendly and professional. The prices are extremely reasonable and fresh local seafood and New Orleans flavor is always on the menu. If your a sports fan this is the place to watch, with over 16 TV’s and a 30-ft. projection screen you won’t miss a play. Visitors and locals alike have a the best time here. Can’t wait to go back this week!

My favorite local bar in the French Quarter! Dog friendly, incredible food and staff! Best place to watch sports, with over 16+ TV’s and a lush courtyard. The food is local favorites and especially the oysters are delicious whether you like them chargrilled or raw. Prices are great too! Can’t wait to come back!

So we went 3 days in a row this past weekend. True story. We stopped in Saturday afternoon on the way back from a socially distanced walk in the QTR, and noticed they had crawfish mac, which is one of my favorites. We decided to grab lunch, I got the crawfish mac & it DID NOT disappoint - in fact, it was great! Also had the stuffed jalapenos and they were amazing as well. Service was also excellent!  Went back Sunday night to grab dinner and watch the Saints game...food & service was great again.  Monday night we knew we wanted something good, we had two great dinners at MRB and we knew they had oysters....so we went back again. Actually had the same server from Saturday, very friendly, and had some amazing chargrilled oysters.  We were very happy with the experience and can't wait to get back!

Best local joint in NOLA's French quarter. Reasonable drinks too. Plenty of indoor big screens and it's never over crowded (unless it's a saints game).  Plus, it boasts TWO courtyards, one with a GIANT movie screen the size of a house. The weekly variety show we host there is easily the best in NOLA.
Loved it! We got crab cakes and the shrimp ceviche. Best in Nola, seriously! Please support this great bar

The most overrated place in the city. The food is crazy expensive. They give you 6 shrimps with barbecue sauce for 15 dollars. 🤦🤦 The shrimps are not good even. The food is bad. Edit: Thanks for letting us know. I will definitely try again.

Simple but quality bar food. We had oysters perfectly fried, crisp outside and not greasy while soft and creamy inside. Proper drinks and beers to suit all tastes. An outside garden in back is lovely but smoking is allowed. Our well behaved dog was welcome in the bar which is snug and cozy and staffed by cheerful people who appear to enjoy their jobs. Television is present but not obtrusive. A delightful alternative to the drinks of Bourbon Street

Got a full refund and walked out! Where I'm from you tip for GOOD service....not just for doing your job.

I came here because it was a cool looking place with lots of TVs that would be chill enough to watch my Purdue Boilermakers play an NCAA tournament game in the late afternoon in peace. If you are in the French Quarter please bypass the tourist trap and head to MRB!! Everything you think you need is here. My first time going was for a crawfish boil and Woodie throws down. I decided from there I would stalk their Instagram only to see they have an amazing selection of food dishes. So last night I went back and the food exceeded my expectations. I had the crab and shrimp egg rolls, butterflied shrimp, and crawfish mac and cheese. Everything was so delicious and the service was phenomenal! Brad is the sweetest and made sure we had a great experience. When I find Ms. Patty, I'm going to give her huge hug because I know she had me in mind when she made that Mac and Cheese. To top it off, we were able to see a free Burlesque and Comedy Show in the courtyard. Now folks, this is all at a dive bar so of course there are beverages to complete this entire experience. Aside from a beer, I also tried their Watermelon and Cucumber Cocktail which is necessary in this NOLA heat. I wrote all of this to say.. go to Woodies MRB, you won't be disappointed. IG: @woodies_at_mrb @barcrawlnola

My husband and I vacationed with our toddler. Many places do not allow anyone under 18 years of age. Because of this we would call ahead to make sure our kid would be allowed to come before making the journey over. The employee asked how old he was and we told him "19 months." He said that would be fine. When we go there one of the employees said we could not have a kid there as they previously got in trouble with the state troopers. When we told her we called (showing her) she replied that someone from the kitchen must of said that finishing with a sorry, cant allow it. It is beyond frustrating when you have your business together and the one who should doesn't. We ended up going to the French Market Restaurant a few businesses down. They were SO nice and accommodating and consistent with their answers.

This is simply the best bar in the French Quarter. Local fare, generous staff, GREAT prices and plenty of entertainment. Giant Movie screen at night, ping pong, pool tables, darts, cornhole boards, multiple giant Jenga sets, and a host of classic board games on the shelves. I relive the best parts of childhood every time I come here which is as often as possible. Ample TV's provide sports and popular shows for fans of all varieties. Come early to watch the live seafood come in every morning then watch them cook it in one of their two laid back patios, one of which is HAUNTED! A must visit!
